# Keep the Docker build context tiny: ignore everything not needed to build
# the C++ binary and run the web server.
#
# What the image actually needs (see Dockerfile):
#   cpp/ (source, minus build/) ; agricola/ ; play.py ; play_web.py ;
#   static/ ; templates/ ; nn_models/cpp_export_best's resolved target dir.

# Version control / tooling
.git
.gitignore
.pytest_cache
.dockerignore
Dockerfile
DEPLOY.md
fly.toml

# Python caches
__pycache__/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# Tests: exclude the suite, but KEEP test_utils.py — agricola/agents/base.py
# (and other agent modules) import `filter_implemented` from it at module load
# (a known code smell). `tests/*` (not `tests/`) lets the two files be
# re-included below so the import resolves in the image.
tests/*
!tests/__init__.py
!tests/test_utils.py
data/
nn_runs/
eval_out/
tuned_configs/
archive/
design_docs/
Rulebooks/
scripts/

# Local C++ build (the Mach-O arm64 artifact; rebuilt for Linux in-image)
cpp/build/

# Docs (none are load-bearing at runtime)
*.md

# Trained-model checkpoints are large and not needed — EXCEPT the C++ exports.
# Ignore all of nn_models/, then un-ignore the whole cpp_export_* family so the
# Dockerfile's EXPORT_DIR build-arg can name ANY of them without an edit here
# (deploy.sh resolves the cpp_export_best symlink to the right one). Only the one
# named by EXPORT_DIR is COPY'd into the image; the rest just ride in the build
# context (~30 MB total, all small). The bare `cpp_export_best` symlink itself is
# left ignored — Docker can't follow it anyway, so it must not be relied on.
nn_models/
!nn_models/cpp_export_*/
